</div>
<div id="p6" class="ltx_para">
<p id="p6.1" class="ltx_p">The presented data therefore does not exclude that the observed effects are due to a combination of a (magnetization independent) rectification, combined with a magneto resistance (Hall) effect. It is however possible to distinguish between this explanation and that of the authors. To support their case they should show that the rectification behaviour observed in the <math id="p6.1.m1.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="V(I)" display="inline"><semantics id="p6.1.m1.1a"><mrow id="p6.1.m1.1.5" xref="p6.1.m1.1.5.cmml"><mi id="p6.1.m1.1.1" xref="p6.1.m1.1.1.cmml">V</mi><mo id="p6.1.m1.1.5.1" xref="p6.1.m1.1.5.1.cmml">â¢</mo><mrow id="p6.1.m1.1.5.2" xref="p6.1.m1.1.5.cmml"><mo stretchy="false" id="p6.1.m1.1.2" xref="p6.1.m1.1.5.cmml">(</mo><mi id="p6.1.m1.1.3" xref="p6.1.m1.1.3.cmml">I</mi><mo stretchy="false" id="p6.1.m1.1.4" xref="p6.1.m1.1.5.cmml">)</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p6.1.m1.1b"><apply id="p6.1.m1.1.5.cmml" xref="p6.1.m1.1.5"><times id="p6.1.m1.1.5.1.cmml" xref="p6.1.m1.1.5.1"></times><ci id="p6.1.m1.1.1.cmml" xref="p6.1.m1.1.1">ğ‘‰</ci><ci id="p6.1.m1.1.3.cmml" xref="p6.1.m1.1.3">ğ¼</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p6.1.m1.1c">italic-V OPEN:( italic-I CLOSE:)</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p6.1.m1.1d">V(I)</annotation></semantics></math> characteristics changes sign, when the magnetization <math id="p6.1.m2.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="M" display="inline"><semantics id="p6.1.m2.1a"><mi id="p6.1.m2.1.1" xref="p6.1.m2.1.1.cmml">M</mi><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p6.1.m2.1b"><ci id="p6.1.m2.1.1.cmml" xref="p6.1.m2.1.1">ğ‘€</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p6.1.m2.1c">italic-M</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p6.1.m2.1d">M</annotation></semantics></math> is reversed. In other words, for a fixed configuration of current and voltage leads, they should show explicitly that the relation <math id="p6.1.m3.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="V(I)_{M}=-V(-I)_{-M}" display="inline"><semantics id="p6.1.m3.1a"><mrow id="p6.1.m3.1.14" xref="p6.1.m3.1.14.cmml"><mrow id="p6.1.m3.1.14.1" xref="p6.1.m3.1.14.1.cmml"><mi id="p6.1.m3.1.1" xref="p6.1.m3.1.1.cmml">V</mi><mo id="p6.1.m3.1.14.1.1" xref="p6.1.m3.1.14.1.1.cmml">â¢</mo><msub id="p6.1.m3.1.14.1.2" xref="p6.1.m3.1.14.1.2.cmml"><mrow id="p6.1.m3.1.14.1.2.2" xref="p6.1.m3.1.14.1.2.cmml"><mo stretchy="false" id="p6.1.m3.1.2" xref="p6.1.m3.1.14.1.2.cmml">(</mo><mi id="p6.1.m3.1.3" xref="p6.1.m3.1.3.cmml">I</mi><mo stretchy="false" id="p6.1.m3.1.4" xref="p6.1.m3.1.14.1.2.cmml">)</mo></mrow><mi id="p6.1.m3.1.5.1" xref="p6.1.m3.1.5.1.cmml">M</mi></msub></mrow><mo id="p6.1.m3.1.6" xref="p6.1.m3.1.6.cmml">=</mo><mrow id="p6.1.m3.1.14.2" xref="p6.1.m3.1.14.2.cmml"><mo id="p6.1.m3.1.7" xref="p6.1.m3.1.7.cmml">-</mo><mrow id="p6.1.m3.1.14.2.1" xref="p6.1.m3.1.14.2.1.cmml"><mi id="p6.1.m3.1.8" xref="p6.1.m3.1.8.cmml">V</mi><mo id="p6.1.m3.1.14.2.1.1" xref="p6.1.m3.1.14.2.1.1.cmml">â¢</mo><msub id="p6.1.m3.1.14.2.1.2" xref="p6.1.m3.1.14.2.1.2.cmml"><mrow id="p6.1.m3.1.14.2.1.2.2" xref="p6.1.m3.1.14.2.1.2.2.2.cmml"><mo stretchy="false" id="p6.1.m3.1.9" xref="p6.1.m3.1.14.2.1.2.2.2.cmml">(</mo><mrow id="p6.1.m3.1.14.2.1.2.2.2" xref="p6.1.m3.1.14.2.1.2.2.2.cmml"><mo id="p6.1.m3.1.10" xref="p6.1.m3.1.10.cmml">-</mo><mi id="p6.1.m3.1.11" xref="p6.1.m3.1.11.cmml">I</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false" id="p6.1.m3.1.12" xref="p6.1.m3.1.14.2.1.2.2.2.cmml">)</mo></mrow><mrow id="p6.1.m3.1.13.1" xref="p6.1.m3.1.13.1.cmml"><mo id="p6.1.m3.1.13.1.1" xref="p6.1.m3.1.13.1.1.cmml">-</mo><mi id="p6.1.m3.1.13.1.2" xref="p6.1.m3.1.13.1.2.cmml">M</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p6.1.m3.1b"><apply id="p6.1.m3.1.14.cmml" xref="p6.1.m3.1.14"><eq id="p6.1.m3.1.6.cmml" xref="p6.1.m3.1.6"></eq><apply id="p6.1.m3.1.14.1.cmml" xref="p6.1.m3.1.14.1"><times id="p6.1.m3.1.14.1.1.c