ion encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p6.1.m4.1c">italic-M</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p6.1.m4.1d">M</annotation></semantics></math> switches direction when the coercive field is exceeded, and a change <math id="p6.1.m5.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\Delta R" display="inline"><semantics id="p6.1.m5.1a"><mrow id="p6.1.m5.1.3" xref="p6.1.m5.1.3.cmml"><mi mathvariant="normal" id="p6.1.m5.1.1" xref="p6.1.m5.1.1.cmml">Î”</mi><mo id="p6.1.m5.1.3.1" xref="p6.1.m5.1.3.1.cmml">â¢</mo><mi id="p6.1.m5.1.2" xref="p6.1.m5.1.2.cmml">R</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p6.1.m5.1b"><apply id="p6.1.m5.1.3.cmml" xref="p6.1.m5.1.3"><times id="p6.1.m5.1.3.1.cmml" xref="p6.1.m5.1.3.1"></times><ci id="p6.1.m5.1.1.cmml" xref="p6.1.m5.1.1">Î”</ci><ci id="p6.1.m5.1.2.cmml" xref="p6.1.m5.1.2">ğ‘…</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p6.1.m5.1c">Delta italic-R</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p6.1.m5.1d">\Delta R</annotation></semantics></math> is observed for positive <math id="p6.1.m6.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="I" display="inline"><semantics id="p6.1.m6.1a"><mi id="p6.1.m6.1.1" xref="p6.1.m6.1.1.cmml">I</mi><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p6.1.m6.1b"><ci id="p6.1.m6.1.1.cmml" xref="p6.1.m6.1.1">ğ¼</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p6.1.m6.1c">italic-I</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p6.1.m6.1d">I</annotation></semantics></math>, an <span id="p6.1.1" class="ltx_text ltx_font_italic">opposite</span> change <math id="p6.1.m7.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="-\Delta R" display="inline"><semantics id="p6.1.m7.1a"><mrow id="p6.1.m7.1.4" xref="p6.1.m7.1.4.cmml"><mo id="p6.1.m7.1.1" xref="p6.1.m7.1.1.cmml">-</mo><mrow id="p6.1.m7.1.4.1" xref="p6.1.m7.1.4.1.cmml"><mi mathvariant="normal" id="p6.1.m7.1.2" xref="p6.1.m7.1.2.cmml">Î”</mi><mo id="p6.1.m7.1.4.1.1" xref="p6.1.m7.1.4.1.1.cmml">â¢</mo><mi id="p6.1.m7.1.3" xref="p6.1.m7.1.3.cmml">R</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p6.1.m7.1b"><apply id="p6.1.m7.1.4.cmml" xref="p6.1.m7.1.4"><minus id="p6.1.m7.1.1.cmml" xref="p6.1.m7.1.1"></minus><apply id="p6.1.m7.1.4.1.cmml" xref="p6.1.m7.1.4.1"><times id="p6.1.m7.1.4.1.1.cmml" xref="p6.1.m7.1.4.1.1"></times><ci id="p6.1.m7.1.2.cmml" xref="p6.1.m7.1.2">Î”</ci><ci id="p6.1.m7.1.3.cmml" xref="p6.1.m7.1.3">ğ‘…</ci></apply></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p6.1.m7.1c">ADDOP:minus Delta italic-R</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p6.1.m7.1d">-\Delta R</annotation></semantics></math> should be observed at negative <math id="p6.1.m8.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="I" display="inline"><semantics id="p6.1.m8.1a"><mi id="p6.1.m8.1.1" xref="p6.1.m8.1.1.cmml">I</mi><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p6.1.m8.1b"><ci id="p6.1.m8.1.1.cmml" xref="p6.1.m8.1.1">ğ¼</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p6.1.m8.1c">italic-I</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="p6.1.m8.1d">I</annotation></semantics></math>. This behaviour can then clearly be distinguished from a Hall effect, which predicts that the change in resistance <math id="p6.1.m9.1" class="ltx_Math" alttext="\Delta R" display="inline"><semantics id="p6.1.m9.1a"><mrow id="p6.1.m9.1.3" xref="p6.1.m9.1.3.cmml"><mi mathvariant="normal" id="p6.1.m9.1.1" xref="p6.1.m9.1.1.cmml">Î”</mi><mo id="p6.1.m9.1.3.1" xref="p6.1.m9.1.3.1.cmml">â¢</mo><mi id="p6.1.m9.1.2" xref="p6.1.m9.1.2.cmml">R</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="p6.1.m9.1b"><apply id="p6.1.m9.1.3.cmml" xref="p6.1.m9.1.3"><times id="p6.1.m9.1.3.1.cmml" xref="p6.1.m9.1.3.1"></times><ci id="p6.1.m9.1.1.cmml" xref="p6.1.m9.1.1">Î”</ci><ci id="p6.1.m9.1.2.cmml" xref="p6.1.m9.1.2">ğ‘…</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="p6.1.m9.1c">Delta italic-R</annotation><annotation encoding=